                            <comment id="13327109" author="dmlloyd" created="Wed, 23 Nov 2016 08:41:44 -0500"  >&lt;p&gt;Also it is objecting to &quot;all&quot; succeeding a &quot;group&quot; reference...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13327122" author="dmlloyd" created="Wed, 23 Nov 2016 08:50:02 -0500"  >&lt;p&gt;The fix for choice-inside-all is to use a substitution group, which requires the elements to be declared in the root schema with an abstract base element for each group, with references to those elements from the &quot;all&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13327128" author="dmlloyd" created="Wed, 23 Nov 2016 08:59:12 -0500"  >&lt;p&gt;I think I see the problem.  All of the errors disappeared again... somehow the IDE is randomly finding or not finding errors in the schema.  Time to switch to xmllint.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
